tering options to narrow down the results based on order characteristics.\\nIt is recommended to set specific clientID&#x27;s when placing different orders, which will be useful to retrieve back a specific order on the v4/orders endpoint\\norders_response = indexer.account.get_subaccount_orders(address, 0) const response = await indexer.account.getSubaccountOrders(ADDRESS, 0);let orders = indexer \\n    .accounts() \\n    .get_subaccount_orders(&amp;subaccount, None) \\n    .await?; \\nSee the API reference the complete method definition.\\nOrderbookFor some trading strategies it is useful to have a continouos view of the orderbook up-to-date. See the Watch Orderbook guide on how to set this up.\\n\",\"title\":\"List Orders\",\"titles\":[\"Trading Data\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/market#get-fills\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Retrieve order fill records for a specific subaccount on the exchange. Fills are matched orders.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"code-group\\\"><div data-title=\\\"Python\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed has-focused\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Python\\\" data-lang=\\\"python\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line focused\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">fills_response </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> indexer.account.get_subaccount_fills(address, </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">0</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">) </span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\" data-lang=\\\"typescript\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> response</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> await</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> indexer.account.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">getSubaccountFills</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">ADDRESS</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">0</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">);</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"Rust\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed has-focused\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Rust\\\" data-lang=\\\"rust\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line focused\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">let</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> fills </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> indexer </span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line focused\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">    .</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">accounts</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">() </span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line focused\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">    .</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">get_subaccount_fills</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">&amp;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">env</span><span style=\\\"c