fo\\\"><strong data-callout-title=\\\"true\\\">Sparklines</strong><p>See also the <a href=\\\"/indexer-client/http/markets/get_sparklines\\\">sparklines method</a> for price history.</p></aside>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/market.mdx#price-history\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nPrice history in the classic candlestick can also be fetched. Data will be organized into a open, high, low, and close (OHLC) prices for some period.\\nfrom dydx_v4_client.indexer.candles_resolution import CandlesResolution\\nresponse = await indexer.markets.get_perpetual_market_candles( \\n    market=&quot;BTC-USD&quot;, resolution=CandlesResolution.ONE_MINUTE\\n) \\nprint(response[&quot;candles&quot;]) const response = await indexer.markets.getPerpetualMarketCandles(&#x27;BTC-USD&#x27;, &#x27;1MIN&#x27;); \\nconsole.log(response.candles); use dydx::indexer::CandleResolution;\\nlet candles = indexer \\n    .markets() \\n    .get_perpetual_market_candles(&amp;&quot;BTC-USD&quot;.into(), CandleResolution::M1, None) \\n    .await?; \\nprintln!(&quot;{candles:?}&quot;); \\nSee the API reference for the complete method definition.\\nSparklinesSee also the sparklines method for price history.\\n\",\"title\":\"Price History\",\"titles\":[\"Trading Data\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/market#get-user-fee-tier\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The Get User Fee Tier function retrieves the perpetual fee tier associated with a specific wallet address, providing information on the user&#x27;s current fee structure.</p>\\n<div class=\\\"code-group\\\"><div data-title=\\\"Python\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Python\\\" data-lang=\\\"python\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">user_fee_tier </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#